<section id="services-hero-532"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/images/brainards-sod-1.jpeg" height="775" width="1920" fetchpriority="high"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-card"><div class="cs-heading-group"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> Rachio. Hydrawise. Rain Bird. B-hyve.</span><h1 class="cs-title">Smart Sprinkler Controller Installation in <span class="cs-color">Las Cruces, NM</span></h1></div><p class="cs-text">WiFi sprinkler controllers that auto-adjust to local weather, lock in your address-parity watering days, and put your whole irrigation system on your phone. We install, program, and guarantee every controller we put on the wall. 19 years in business. 500+ projects installed. Workmanship guarantee.</p><div class="cs-button-group"><a href="/contact/" class="cs-button-solid cs-nav-button">Get a Free Estimate</a> <a href="tel:575-635-8883" class="cs-phone-button"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/phone.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> (575) 635-8883</a></div></div></div></section><section id="services-intro-109"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/fern.svg" height="483" width="224" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-fern cs-fern-right"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/fern.svg" height="483" width="224" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-fern cs-fern-left"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-row"><img alt="WiFi-managed drip irrigation zone installed by Brainard's Greenscapes in Las Cruces, NM" decoding="async" src="/assets/images/brainards-drip-irrigation.jpeg" height="686" width="480" loading="lazy"><div class="cs-content"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> What You Get</span><h2 class="cs-title">A WiFi Sprinkler Controller, Programmed Correctly</h2><p class="cs-text">A smart sprinkler controller swaps your old mechanical or digital timer for a WiFi-connected unit that adjusts watering based on weather, season, and city rules. Rain skip, wind skip, freeze skip, and a phone app come standard. EPA WaterSense certifies most of these as water-saving devices, and Las Cruces Utilities runs occasional rebates on certified models. The hardware is straightforward. The wins come from programming it correctly the first time.</p><ul class="cs-bullets"><li>Weather-based scheduling tuned to Las Cruces ET data, not a generic national average.</li><li>Address parity locked into the city watering schedule on day one.</li><li>Phone control: start a zone, skip a day, watch usage from anywhere.</li><li>Indoor or outdoor mounting depending on your existing setup.</li><li>Compatible with existing sprinkler valves, drip zones, and master valves.</li></ul><div class="cs-button-group"><a href="/contact/" class="cs-button-solid cs-nav-button">Schedule a Free Estimate</a> <a href="tel:575-635-8883" class="cs-phone-button"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/phone.svg" height="13" width="13" aria-hidden="true"> (575) 635-8883</a></div></div></div><ul class="cs-card-group"><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-icon-wrap"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/icon-landscape-design.svg" height="56" width="56" aria-hidden="true" loading="lazy"></div><h3 class="cs-item-title">Weather-Based Scheduling</h3><p class="cs-item-text">Auto-skip on rainy or windy days. Seasonal adjust dials run times up in July and back in October. Set it and forget it.</p></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-icon-wrap"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/images/icon-irrigation-56.webp" height="56" width="56" aria-hidden="true" loading="lazy"></div><h3 class="cs-item-title">Phone Control</h3><p class="cs-item-text">Start a zone, skip a day, change a schedule from anywhere. iOS and Android apps from every brand we install.</p></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-icon-wrap"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/icon-xeriscaping.svg" height="56" width="56" aria-hidden="true" loading="lazy"></div><h3 class="cs-item-title">Ordinance Lock</h3><p class="cs-item-text">Address-parity days, no-Monday rule, and the 10 a.m. to 6 p.m. summer blackout all programmed before we leave.</p></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-icon-wrap"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/icon-maintenance.svg" height="56" width="56" aria-hidden="true" loading="lazy"></div><h3 class="cs-item-title">Usage Tracking</h3><p class="cs-item-text">See gallons used per zone per week. Spot a leak, a stuck valve, or a runaway schedule before it shows on your bill.</p></li></ul></div></section><section id="services-process-148"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-header"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> How We Work</span><h2 class="cs-title">Our 5-Step Smart Controller Installation Process</h2></div><div class="cs-grid-wrap"><ul class="cs-card-group"><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-icon-wrap"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/icon-lightbulb.svg" height="40" width="40" aria-hidden="true" loading="lazy"></div><h3 class="cs-item-title">System Check</h3><p class="cs-item-text">We look at your existing controller, count zones, check WiFi reach to the install spot, and confirm the unit you want fits your setup.</p></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-icon-wrap"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/icon-lightbulb.svg" height="40" width="40" aria-hidden="true" loading="lazy"></div><h3 class="cs-item-title">Pick the Controller</h3><p class="cs-item-text">Rachio, Hunter Hydrawise, Rain Bird with LNK WiFi, or Orbit B-hyve. We help match the unit to your zones, budget, and rebate eligibility.</p></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-icon-wrap"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/icon-lightbulb.svg" height="40" width="40" aria-hidden="true" loading="lazy"></div><h3 class="cs-item-title">Install &amp; Wire</h3><p class="cs-item-text">We label every zone, swap the unit, mount indoor or outdoor, and clean up wiring. Old controllers get hauled off if you want them gone.</p></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-icon-wrap"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/icon-lightbulb.svg" height="40" width="40" aria-hidden="true" loading="lazy"></div><h3 class="cs-item-title">WiFi &amp; Programming</h3><p class="cs-item-text">Pair to your WiFi, install the app on your phone, set address-parity days, lock out the 10 a.m. to 6 p.m. window, and load seasonal adjust.</p></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-icon-wrap"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/icon-lightbulb.svg" height="40" width="40" aria-hidden="true" loading="lazy"></div><h3 class="cs-item-title">Walkthrough</h3><p class="cs-item-text">We run every zone live, show you the app, and hand off a watering plan that matches the city ordinance.</p></li></ul><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/leaf-down.svg" height="184" width="168" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-vine cs-vine-1"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/leaf-up.svg" height="184" width="168" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-vine cs-vine-2"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/leaf-down.svg" height="184" width="168" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-vine cs-vine-3"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/leaf-up.svg" height="184" width="168" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-vine cs-vine-4"></div></div></section><section id="services-signs-870"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-content"><div class="cs-header"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> Reasons to Upgrade</span><h2 class="cs-title">Why Las Cruces Homeowners Switch to Smart Controllers</h2><p class="cs-text">Most calls we get for smart sprinkler controllers start with one of these. Replacing a basic timer with a weather-based controller solves the problem at the source.</p></div><div class="cs-button-group"><a href="/contact/" class="cs-button-solid cs-nav-button">Tell Us About Your Setup</a> <a href="tel:575-635-8883" class="cs-phone-button"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/phone.svg" height="13" width="13" aria-hidden="true"> (575) 635-8883</a></div><ul class="cs-signs"><li class="cs-sign"><h3 class="cs-sign-title">Wrong-Day Watering Tickets</h3><p class="cs-sign-text">Old timers do not know what day it is, let alone what address parity you have. Smart controllers lock in Tue/Thu/Sat or Wed/Fri/Sun and never miss.</p></li><li class="cs-sign"><h3 class="cs-sign-title">Sprinklers Running in the Rain</h3><p class="cs-sign-text">Manual timers run on schedule no matter the weather. Smart controllers pull live forecasts and skip rain, wind, and freeze events automatically.</p></li><li class="cs-sign"><h3 class="cs-sign-title">Climbing Summer Water Bills</h3><p class="cs-sign-text">A controller programmed once in March is wrong by July. Seasonal adjust dials run times up and down by month, automatically.</p></li><li class="cs-sign"><h3 class="cs-sign-title">Out of Town and Worried</h3><p class="cs-sign-text">Phone control means you can pause watering during a vacation, or run a single zone if a neighbor mentions a brown spot.</p></li><li class="cs-sign"><h3 class="cs-sign-title">Old Controller Box Is Failing</h3><p class="cs-sign-text">Faded screens, stuck buttons, lost programs after a power blip. A failing controller is a leaking yard waiting to happen.</p></li><li class="cs-sign"><h3 class="cs-sign-title">New Sprinkler or Drip System</h3><p class="cs-sign-text">Pair a smart controller with a fresh install and the system runs at peak efficiency from day one. Most new installs we do include this by default.</p></li></ul></div><img alt="Healthy lawn maintained by Brainard's Greenscapes smart sprinkler controller installation in Las Cruces" decoding="async" src="/assets/images/brainards-sod-2.jpeg" height="996" width="616" loading="lazy"></div></section><section id="services-region-450"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-header"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> Brands We Install</span><h2 class="cs-title">WiFi Sprinkler Controllers, Brand by Brand</h2></div><div class="cs-body"><p class="cs-text">We install, program, and guarantee every major smart sprinkler controller line. Pick by features, pick by your existing system, or let us match it to your zone count and budget.</p><p class="cs-text"><strong>Rachio (Gen 3 / 3e):</strong> the easiest smart sprinkler controller for most homeowners. Strong app, weather intelligence, EPA WaterSense certified, and broadly supported by utility rebate programs. Available in 4, 8, and 16-zone units.</p><p class="cs-text"><strong>Hunter Hydrawise:</strong> the natural pick if your existing system is built on Hunter parts. Hydrawise WiFi drops into existing Pro-C controllers via an upgrade module, and Hunter also makes dedicated Hydrawise units (Pro-HC, HCC). Pro-HC ships in 6, 12, and 24-station residential models. HCC expands up to 54 stations for larger or commercial sites.</p><p class="cs-text"><strong>Rain Bird ESP-Me / ESP-TM2 with LNK WiFi:</strong> the right call if your installer used Rain Bird and you want to keep parts consistent. Add the LNK module and you get phone control, seasonal adjust, and rain skip without replacing the whole controller.</p><p class="cs-text"><strong>Orbit B-hyve:</strong> a solid budget option, especially the B-hyve XR. The XR is sold in 8-zone and 16-zone models; smaller standard B-hyve units cover 4 and 12-zone setups. Indoor and outdoor enclosures.</p><p class="cs-text"><strong>Replacing a legacy controller:</strong> we routinely retire Toro, K-Rain, Irritrol, and 1990s-era Hunter and Rain Bird mechanical timers. The wires from your existing valves move directly into the new unit. No re-trenching required.</p><p class="cs-text">Not sure which to pick? On a free estimate visit we look at your existing setup, your WiFi reach, and any rebates that apply, then make a recommendation tied to your zones and run times.</p><a href="/contact/" class="cs-button-solid cs-nav-button">Get a Recommendation</a></div><img alt="Smart sprinkler controller installation by Brainard's Greenscapes in Las Cruces, NM" decoding="async" src="/assets/images/brainards-misc-1.jpeg" height="995" width="440" loading="lazy"></div></section><section id="services-why-353"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/images/leaves-pattern.jpeg" height="1840" width="1920" loading="lazy"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/fern.svg" height="483" width="224" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-fern"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-header"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> Why Choose Us</span><h2 class="cs-title">Why Las Cruces Trusts Brainard’s for Smart Controllers</h2><p class="cs-intro">A smart sprinkler controller pays back only when it is programmed correctly. We install the unit, but we also do the harder work: locking the city ordinance into the schedule, tuning seasonal adjust to your plant zones, and verifying every valve. The hardware is the easy part.</p></div><div class="cs-gallery" aria-hidden="true"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/images/brainards-xeriscaping-19.jpeg" height="594" width="460" loading="lazy"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/images/brainards-sod-4.jpeg" height="439" width="330" loading="lazy"></div><ul class="cs-feature-list"><li class="cs-feature"><div class="cs-feature-head"><h3 class="cs-feature-title">All Major Brands</h3><svg height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.75" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-feature-arrow"><path d="M4 12 L12 4"></path><path d="M6 4 L12 4 L12 10"></path></svg></div><p class="cs-feature-text">Rachio, Hunter Hydrawise, Rain Bird LNK, and Orbit B-hyve. Picked to match your existing system, not a single brand we’re tied to.</p></li><li class="cs-feature"><div class="cs-feature-head"><h3 class="cs-feature-title">Programmed for the Ordinance</h3><svg height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.75" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-feature-arrow"><path d="M4 12 L12 4"></path><path d="M6 4 L12 4 L12 10"></path></svg></div><p class="cs-feature-text">Address-parity days, Monday lockout, and the summer 10 a.m. to 6 p.m. blackout all dialed in before we leave the property.</p></li><li class="cs-feature"><div class="cs-feature-head"><h3 class="cs-feature-title">Walkthrough Included</h3><svg height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.75" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-feature-arrow"><path d="M4 12 L12 4"></path><path d="M6 4 L12 4 L12 10"></path></svg></div><p class="cs-feature-text">We hand off the phone app working, every zone labeled, and a watering plan you can read. Call us back any time you want to tune it.</p></li><li class="cs-feature"><div class="cs-feature-head"><h3 class="cs-feature-title">Workmanship Guarantee</h3><svg height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.75" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-feature-arrow"><path d="M4 12 L12 4"></path><path d="M6 4 L12 4 L12 10"></path></svg></div><p class="cs-feature-text">Installation work guaranteed for as long as you own the home. Plus full manufacturer warranties from Rachio, Hunter, Rain Bird, and Orbit.</p></li></ul><a href="/contact/" class="cs-quote-button">Get a Free Estimate</a></div></section><section id="services-pricing-219"><div class="cs-container"><article class="cs-price-card"><h2 class="cs-price-title">Smart Sprinkler Controller Installation Cost</h2><span class="cs-price-label">Typical Range</span> <span class="cs-price-amount"><span class="cs-price-symbol">$</span>350–$950</span><p class="cs-price-text">Smart sprinkler controller installation typically runs $350 to $950 installed in Las Cruces. The range covers the controller itself ($150 to $450), labor for swapping the old timer, cleaning up zone wiring, indoor or outdoor mounting, pairing to WiFi, and programming the city watering schedule. WaterSense-certified Rachio and Hydrawise models often qualify for utility rebates that knock $50 to $100 off the controller cost.</p><ul class="cs-price-bullets"><li>Free on-site estimate, always.</li><li>Itemized quote with the controller you choose.</li><li>Workmanship guarantee on every install.</li></ul><a href="/contact/" class="cs-price-link">Request a Custom Quote <svg height="14" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="14" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.75" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M4 12 L12 4"></path><path d="M6 4 L12 4 L12 10"></path></svg></a></article><article class="cs-diff-card"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/images/leaves-pattern.jpeg" height="629" width="572" loading="lazy"><h2 class="cs-diff-title">The Brainard’s Difference</h2><ul class="cs-diff-list"><li class="cs-diff-item"><span class="cs-diff-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="20" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"><path d="M12 3 V21"></path><path d="M8 8 H16"></path></svg></span><div class="cs-diff-body"><h3 class="cs-diff-name">Faith-Centered</h3><p class="cs-diff-text">Honest pricing, clear communication, and follow-through on every install. We do what we say.</p></div></li><li class="cs-diff-item"><span class="cs-diff-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="20" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"><path d="M12 3 L20 6 V12 C20 16.5 16.5 20 12 21 C7.5 20 4 16.5 4 12 V6 Z"></path></svg></span><div class="cs-diff-body"><h3 class="cs-diff-name">Workmanship Guarantee</h3><p class="cs-diff-text">Wiring and mount work guaranteed for as long as you own the home. Plus full manufacturer warranties on every controller.</p></div></li><li class="cs-diff-item"><span class="cs-diff-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="20" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"><path d="M12 2 C8 2 5 5 5 9 C5 14 12 22 12 22 C12 22 19 14 19 9 C19 5 16 2 12 2 Z"></path><circle cx="12" cy="9" r="2.5"></circle></svg></span><div class="cs-diff-body"><h3 class="cs-diff-name">Locally Rooted</h3><p class="cs-diff-text">Programming tuned to Las Cruces ET data, the city ordinance, and the seasons of the Mesilla Valley.</p></div></li></ul></article></div></section><section id="services-local-360"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-header"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> Built for the Ordinance</span><h2 class="cs-title">Programmed to the Las Cruces Watering Ordinance</h2><p class="cs-text">Every controller we install gets programmed to the city schedule before we leave. No homework on your end.</p></div><ul class="cs-local-list"><li><strong>Address parity:</strong> even-numbered addresses water Tue / Thu / Sat. Odd-numbered water Wed / Fri / Sun.</li><li><strong>Monday lockout:</strong> every controller skips Monday by default.</li><li><strong>April 1–Sept 30:</strong> no watering between 10 a.m. and 6 p.m. We schedule pre-dawn and post-dusk run times only.</li><li><strong>Rain skip:</strong> auto-skip thresholds set so a quarter-inch of rain pauses the next cycle.</li><li><strong>Seasonal adjust:</strong> run times scale up and back through the year to match Las Cruces ET.</li><li><strong>WaterSense rebate:</strong> we flag eligible Rachio and Hydrawise units so you can apply for utility rebates when they are running.</li></ul><p class="cs-text cs-text-footer">Source: <a href="https://lascruces.gov/property/utilities/utility-services/water-conservation/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Las Cruces Utilities Water Conservation Program</a>.</p></div></section><section id="service-areas-825"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/fern.svg" height="483" width="224" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-fern"><div class="cs-container"><aside class="cs-info-card"><div class="cs-info-head"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <svg height="10" viewBox="0 0 48 10" width="48" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.4" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"><path d="M2 5 H42"></path><path d="M36 1 L42 5 L36 9"></path></svg> Where We Install</span><h2 class="cs-title">Las Cruces &amp; the Mesilla Valley</h2></div><div class="cs-info-body"><p class="cs-text">We install smart sprinkler controllers throughout Las Cruces and the Mesilla Valley, roughly within 30 miles of our office.</p><ul class="cs-locations"><li><a href="/service-areas/las-cruces-nm/">Smart Controllers in Las Cruces, NM</a></li><li><a href="/service-areas/mesilla-nm/">Smart Controllers in Mesilla, NM</a></li><li><a href="/service-areas/dona-ana-nm/">Smart Controllers in Doña Ana, NM</a></li><li><a href="/service-areas/sonoma-ranch-nm/">Smart Controllers in Sonoma Ranch, NM</a></li><li><a href="/service-areas/picacho-hills-nm/">Smart Controllers in Picacho Hills, NM</a></li><li><a href="/service-areas/east-mesa-nm/">Smart Controllers in East Mesa, NM</a></li><li><a href="/service-areas/anthony-nm/">Smart Controllers in Anthony, NM</a></li><li><a href="/service-areas/sunland-park-nm/">Smart Controllers in Sunland Park, NM</a></li></ul></div><img alt="Brainard's Greenscapes smart sprinkler controller installation in Las Cruces" decoding="async" src="/assets/images/brainards-xeriscaping-20.jpeg" height="130" width="428" loading="lazy"><div class="cs-office"><h3 class="cs-office-heading">Our Office Location</h3><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/Brainard's+Greenscapes/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x0:0x3c69d063ef4f24?sa=X&amp;ved=1t:2428&amp;ictx=111" class="cs-office-address" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Las Cruces, NM </a><span class="cs-office-underline" aria-hidden="true"></span> <a href="/service-areas/" class="cs-office-button">View All Service Areas</a></div></aside><div class="cs-map"><iframe allowfullscreen="" height="934" loading="lazy" referrerpolicy="no-referrer-when-downgrade" src="https://www.google.com/maps?q=Las%20Cruces+NM&amp;output=embed" title="Map of Las Cruces, NM service area" width="960"></iframe></div></div></section><section id="testimonials-515" class="cs-reviews-carousel"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/images/leaves-pattern.jpeg" height="1072" width="1920" loading="lazy"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/fern.svg" height="483" width="224" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-fern"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-header"><div class="cs-content"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> Testimonials</span><h2 class="cs-title">Let’s Talk About Your Outdoor Vision</h2></div><div class="cs-controls"><button class="cs-arrow cs-arrow-prev" aria-label="Previous reviews" type="button" data-reviews-prev=""><svg height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="16" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M15 18l-6-6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></button> <button class="cs-arrow cs-arrow-next" aria-label="Next reviews" type="button" data-reviews-next=""><svg height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="16" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M9 6l6 6-6 6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></button></div></div><ul class="cs-card-group" data-reviews-track=""><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-stars" role="img" aria-label="5 out of 5 stars"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"></div><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/quote-green.svg" height="51" width="51" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-quote-icon"><blockquote class="cs-item-text">David was incredibly knowledgeable and helpful. He patiently answered all of my questions about the plants and trees around my home and provided valuable insights into the issues I was facing. His friendly demeanor and expertise made the experience enjoyable and informative. I highly recommend him</blockquote><div class="cs-item-footer"><div class="cs-author"><span class="cs-name">Alexis Silva</span> <span class="cs-role">a year ago</span></div><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103948667181155023139/reviews" class="cs-google-link" aria-label="View review on Google" rel="noopener" target="_blank"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/google-g.svg" height="30" width="30"></a></div></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-stars" role="img" aria-label="5 out of 5 stars"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"></div><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/quote-green.svg" height="51" width="51" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-quote-icon"><blockquote class="cs-item-text">We had a great experience with David. We used him for one of our rental properties in Las Cruces and will definitely be using him again for the next one. Everything from start to finish was professional and timely. Highly recommend.</blockquote><div class="cs-item-footer"><div class="cs-author"><span class="cs-name">Travis Boyle</span> <span class="cs-role">a year ago</span></div><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108997149124684397289/reviews" class="cs-google-link" aria-label="View review on Google" rel="noopener" target="_blank"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/google-g.svg" height="30" width="30"></a></div></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-stars" role="img" aria-label="5 out of 5 stars"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"></div><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/quote-green.svg" height="51" width="51" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-quote-icon"><blockquote class="cs-item-text">Brainard's Greenscapes recently revamped my backyard with rock landscaping. I couldn't be happier with how the project turned out. From start to finish David's team was professional, punctual, and courteous. They helped me select the the right materials and offered additional design ideas. The quality of work was EXCELLENT. I highly recommend David's team to all homeowners in Las Cruces looking for reliable landscaping company. The picture below is of my backyard 1 year later and there is still no weeds! I can't think Braindard's Greenscapes enough.</blockquote><div class="cs-item-footer"><div class="cs-author"><span class="cs-name">Matthew Lee</span> <span class="cs-role">a year ago</span></div><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112275232644298872770/reviews" class="cs-google-link" aria-label="View review on Google" rel="noopener" target="_blank"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/google-g.svg" height="30" width="30"></a></div></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-stars" role="img" aria-label="5 out of 5 stars"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"></div><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/quote-green.svg" height="51" width="51" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-quote-icon"><blockquote class="cs-item-text">I had a sprinkler emergency and David came out immediately; found an effective solution to get me through until the major repairs could be made; and took care to make sure my house wasn't without water in the meantime. I am so grateful for his kindness and professionalism. He demonstrated considerable expertise and decisive decision making that got me through this emergencies with minimal stress. He is trustworthy and will be the first one I'll call on any future sprinkler needs.</blockquote><div class="cs-item-footer"><div class="cs-author"><span class="cs-name">Jennifer Wees-Schkade</span> <span class="cs-role">2 years ago</span></div><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113879630740524577871/reviews" class="cs-google-link" aria-label="View review on Google" rel="noopener" target="_blank"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/google-g.svg" height="30" width="30"></a></div></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-stars" role="img" aria-label="5 out of 5 stars"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"></div><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/quote-green.svg" height="51" width="51" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-quote-icon"><blockquote class="cs-item-text">Brainard’s Greenscapes is a top notch business. I have called on them on several occasions to fix issues with my irrigation system and for new projects. David, the owner, is a sincere, honest individual, who cares about his business and his customers. His employees are also kind and always professional. They are punctual and complete the job as promised and clean up after they are done. I am very pleased with David and his company and have recommended him to my neighbor, who is also a widow because I know he is honest and will not take advantage of her. David is a good guy and I recommend that you give him a call and see for yourself.</blockquote><div class="cs-item-footer"><div class="cs-author"><span class="cs-name">George Rodriguez</span> <span class="cs-role">6 years ago</span></div><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113926776793747685994/reviews" class="cs-google-link" aria-label="View review on Google" rel="noopener" target="_blank"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/google-g.svg" height="30" width="30"></a></div></li></ul></div></section><section id="faq-506"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/fern.svg" height="483" width="224" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-fern"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-content"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> FAQ</span><h2 class="cs-title">Smart Sprinkler Controller FAQs</h2></div><ul class="cs-faq-list"><li class="cs-faq-item"><details class="cs-faq"><summary class="cs-faq-summary"><span class="cs-faq-question">What is a smart sprinkler controller?</span> <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></span></summary><div class="cs-faq-body"><p>A smart sprinkler controller is a WiFi-enabled timer that replaces a traditional sprinkler clock. It connects to local weather data, soil moisture, and an app on your phone, and adjusts watering automatically based on rain, wind, and the season. Most models also let you skip watering on bad days, run individual zones manually, and check usage history. EPA WaterSense certifies many of these as water-saving devices.</p></div></details></li><li class="cs-faq-item"><details class="cs-faq"><summary class="cs-faq-summary"><span class="cs-faq-question">Is a smart sprinkler controller worth it in Las Cruces?</span> <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></span></summary><div class="cs-faq-body"><p>Yes. Las Cruces enforces strict watering days and hours, and weather-based controllers handle that automatically. Most homeowners save 20% to 50% on outdoor water use the first full season, which usually pays the controller back in one to two years. The controller also keeps you in compliance with the city ordinance without manual reprogramming each season.</p></div></details></li><li class="cs-faq-item"><details class="cs-faq"><summary class="cs-faq-summary"><span class="cs-faq-question">Which smart sprinkler controller is best?</span> <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></span></summary><div class="cs-faq-body"><p>Rachio (Gen 3 / 3e) and Hunter Hydrawise are the strongest options for most Las Cruces homes. Rachio is easier to use and well-supported by the WaterSense rebate ecosystem. Hunter Hydrawise integrates cleanly with existing Hunter and Pro-C systems and is a good fit if your installer used Hunter parts. Rain Bird with the LNK WiFi module is a good choice for existing Rain Bird ESP-Me or ESP-TM2 controllers. We install all three plus Orbit B-hyve.</p></div></details></li><li class="cs-faq-item"><details class="cs-faq"><summary class="cs-faq-summary"><span class="cs-faq-question">How much does smart sprinkler controller installation cost?</span> <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></span></summary><div class="cs-faq-body"><p>Smart sprinkler controller installation typically runs $350 to $950 installed in Las Cruces. The range covers the controller itself ($150 to $450), labor for swapping the old timer, cleaning up zone wiring, mounting indoor or outdoor, pairing to WiFi, and programming the city watering schedule. WaterSense-certified models often qualify for utility rebates.</p></div></details></li><li class="cs-faq-item"><details class="cs-faq"><summary class="cs-faq-summary"><span class="cs-faq-question">Can I install a smart sprinkler controller myself?</span> <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></span></summary><div class="cs-faq-body"><p>You can, but we replace a lot of DIY installs that ended up watering on the wrong days, missing zones, or cycling the lawn during the city’s blackout window. The hardware is straightforward to wire. The harder parts are pairing the unit to a finicky WiFi signal in a garage or shed, programming address-parity days correctly, and matching seasonal run times to plant zones. We do the whole thing in about an hour and program it in front of you.</p></div></details></li><li class="cs-faq-item"><details class="cs-faq"><summary class="cs-faq-summary"><span class="cs-faq-question">Will a smart controller work with my existing sprinkler system?</span> <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></span></summary><div class="cs-faq-body"><p>Almost always. A smart controller connects to the same zone wires as your old timer, so any standard residential sprinkler system from the last 30 years is compatible. We label every zone, swap the unit, and verify each valve before we leave. For older mechanical timers we sometimes add a relay or rewire the master valve depending on the setup.</p></div></details></li><li class="cs-faq-item"><details class="cs-faq"><summary class="cs-faq-summary"><span class="cs-faq-question">Do smart sprinkler controllers handle the Las Cruces watering ordinance?</span> <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></span></summary><div class="cs-faq-body"><p>Yes, when programmed correctly. We set the controller to your address parity (Tue/Thu/Sat for even, Wed/Fri/Sun for odd), block Mondays, and lock out the 10 a.m. to 6 p.m. window from April through September. Smart features (rain skip, seasonal adjust) layer on top of those rules. You stay in compliance every month of the year without thinking about it.</p></div></details></li></ul></div></section><section id="services-related-184"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-content"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> Related Services</span><h2 class="cs-title">Pair Your Smart Controller with These Services</h2><p class="cs-text">A controller upgrade gets even better paired with the right zone work underneath it.</p></div><ul class="cs-related-list"><li class="cs-related-card"><a href="/services/irrigation/sprinkler-systems/" class="cs-related-link"><h3 class="cs-related-title">Sprinkler Systems</h3><p class="cs-related-text">New pop-up and rotary zones designed around the same WiFi controller.</p><span class="cs-related-arrow" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.75"><path d="M4 12 L12 4"></path><path d="M6 4 L12 4 L12 10"></path></svg></span></a></li><li class="cs-related-card"><a href="/services/irrigation/drip-irrigation/" class="cs-related-link"><h3 class="cs-related-title">Drip Irrigation</h3><p class="cs-related-text">Drip zones for trees, shrubs, and beds, programmed alongside your turf zones.</p><span class="cs-related-arrow" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.75"><path d="M4 12 L12 4"></path><path d="M6 4 L12 4 L12 10"></path></svg></span></a></li><li class="cs-related-card"><a href="/services/irrigation/sprinkler-repair/" class="cs-related-link"><h3 class="cs-related-title">Sprinkler Repair</h3><p class="cs-related-text">Diagnose stuck valves, broken heads, and leaks the controller is flagging.</p><span class="cs-related-arrow" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.75"><path d="M4 12 L12 4"></path><path d="M6 4 L12 4 L12 10"></path></svg></span></a></li><li class="cs-related-card"><a href="/services/landscaping/xeriscaping/" class="cs-related-link"><h3 class="cs-related-title">Xeriscaping</h3><p class="cs-related-text">Drought-tolerant landscapes that pair naturally with WiFi-controlled drip.</p><span class="cs-related-arrow" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.75"><path d="M4 12 L12 4"></path><path d="M6 4 L12 4 L12 10"></path></svg></span></a></li><li class="cs-related-card"><a href="/services/landscape-maintenance/" class="cs-related-link"><h3 class="cs-related-title">Landscape Maintenance</h3><p class="cs-related-text">Seasonal controller adjustments, fall blowouts, and spring start-ups.</p><span class="cs-related-arrow" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.75"><path d="M4 12 L12 4"></path><path d="M6 4 L12 4 L12 10"></path></svg></span></a></li></ul></div></section><section id="lets-talk-318"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/talk-tree.svg" height="457" width="427" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-tree"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/talk-bird-1.svg" height="20" width="64" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-bird cs-bird-1"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/talk-bird-2.svg" height="15" width="56" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-bird cs-bird-2"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/talk-bird-3.svg" height="15" width="46" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-bird cs-bird-3"><div class="cs-container"><h2 class="cs-title">Ready to Put Your Sprinklers on Your Phone?</h2><a href="/contact/" class="cs-talk-button">Get a Free Estimate</a></div><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/talk-grass-top.svg" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-grass"></section>
